272{
273 changes += "<table>";
274 for (const ConfigSubstitution& conf_substitution : conf_substitutions) {
275 wxString new_val;
276 const ConfigOptionDef* def = conf_substitution.opt_def;
277 if (!def)
278 continue;
279 switch (def->type) {
280 case coEnum:
281 {
282 const std::vector<std::string>& labels = def->enum_labels;
283 const std::vector<std::string>& values = def->enum_values;
284 int val = conf_substitution.new_value->getInt();
285
286 bool is_infill = def->opt_key == "top_surface_pattern" ||
287 def->opt_key == "bottom_surface_pattern" ||
288 def->opt_key == "internal_solid_infill_pattern" ||
289 def->opt_key == "sparse_infill_pattern";
290
291 // Each infill doesn't use all list of infill declared in PrintConfig.hpp.
292 // So we should "convert" val to the correct one
293 if (is_infill) {
294 for (const auto& key_val : *def->enum_keys_map)
295 if ((int)key_val.second == val) {
296 auto it = std::find(values.begin(), values.end(), key_val.first);
297 if (it == values.end())
298 break;
299 auto idx = it - values.begin();
300 new_val = wxString("\"") + values[idx] + "\"" + " (" + from_u8(_utf8(labels[idx])) + ")";
301 break;
302 }
303 if (new_val.IsEmpty()) {
304 assert(false);
305 new_val = _L("Undefined");
306 }
307 }
308 else
309 new_val = wxString("\"") + values[val] + "\"" + " (" + from_u8(_utf8(labels[val])) + ")";
310 break;
311 }
312 case coBool:
313 new_val = conf_substitution.new_value->getBool() ? "true" : "false";
314 break;
315 case coBools:
316 if (conf_substitution.new_value->nullable())
317 for (const char v : static_cast<const ConfigOptionBoolsNullable*>(conf_substitution.new_value.get())->values)
318 new_val += std::string(v == ConfigOptionBoolsNullable::nil_value() ? "nil" : v ? "true" : "false") + ", ";
319 else
320 for (const char v : static_cast<const ConfigOptionBools*>(conf_substitution.new_value.get())->values)
321 new_val += std::string(v ? "true" : "false") + ", ";
322 if (! new_val.empty())
323 new_val.erase(new_val.begin() + new_val.size() - 2, new_val.end());
324 break;
325 default:
326 assert(false);
327 }
328
329 changes += format_wxstr("<tr><td><b>\"%1%\" (%2%)</b></td><td>: ", def->opt_key, _(def->label)) +
330 format_wxstr(_L("%1% was replaced with %2%"), bold_string(conf_substitution.old_value), bold(new_val)) +
331 "</td></tr>";
332 }
333 changes += "</table>";

242{
243 wxHtmlWindow* html = new wxHtmlWindow(parent, wxID_ANY, wxDefaultPosition, wxDefaultSize, wxHW_SCROLLBAR_AUTO);
244 html->SetBackgroundColour(StateColor::darkModeColorFor(*wxWHITE));

246 // count lines in the message
247 int msg_lines = 0;
248 if (!monospaced_font) {
249 int line_len = 55;// count of symbols in one line
250 int start_line = 0;
251 for (auto i = msg.begin(); i != msg.end(); ++i) {
252 if (*i == '\n') {
253 int cur_line_len = i - msg.begin() - start_line;
254 start_line = i - msg.begin();
255 if (cur_line_len == 0 || line_len > cur_line_len)
256 msg_lines++;
257 else
258 msg_lines += std::lround((double)(cur_line_len) / line_len);
259 }

261 msg_lines++;
262 }

265 wxFont monospace = wxGetApp().code_font();
266 wxColour text_clr = wxGetApp().get_label_clr_default();
267 wxColour bgr_clr = parent->GetBackgroundColour(); //wxSystemSettings::GetColour(wxSYS_COLOUR_WINDOW);
268 auto text_clr_str = wxString::Format(wxT("#%02X%02X%02X"), text_clr.Red(), text_clr.Green(), text_clr.Blue());
269 auto bgr_clr_str = wxString::Format(wxT("#%02X%02X%02X"), bgr_clr.Red(), bgr_clr.Green(), bgr_clr.Blue());
270 const int font_size = font.GetPointSize();
271 int size[] = { font_size, font_size, font_size, font_size, font_size, font_size, font_size };
272 html->SetFonts(font.GetFaceName(), monospace.GetFaceName(), size);
273 html->SetBorders(2);
274
275 // calculate html page size from text
276 wxSize page_size;
277 int em = wxGetApp().em_unit();
278 if (!wxGetApp().mainframe) {
279 // If mainframe is nullptr, it means that GUI_App::on_init_inner() isn't completed
280 // (We just show information dialog about configuration version now)
281 // And as a result the em_unit value wasn't created yet
282 // So, calculate it from the scale factor of Dialog
283#if defined(__WXGTK__)
284 // Linux specific issue : get_dpi_for_window(this) still doesn't responce to the Display's scale in new wxWidgets(3.1.3).
285 // So, initialize default width_unit according to the width of the one symbol ("m") of the currently active font of this window.
286 em = std::max<size_t>(10, parent->GetTextExtent("m").x - 1);
287#else
288 double scale_factor = (double)get_dpi_for_window(parent) / (double)DPI_DEFAULT;
289 em = std::max<size_t>(10, 10.0f * scale_factor);
290#endif // __WXGTK__
291 }
292
293 // if message containes the table
294 if (msg.Contains("<tr>")) {
295 int lines = msg.Freq('\n') + 1;
296 int pos = 0;
297 while (pos < (int)msg.Len() && pos != wxNOT_FOUND) {
298 pos = msg.find("<tr>", pos + 1);
299 lines += 2;
300 }
301 int page_height = std::min(int(font.GetPixelSize().y+2) * lines, 68 * em);
302 page_size = wxSize(68 * em, page_height);
303 }
304 else {
305 wxClientDC dc(parent);
306 wxSize msg_sz = dc.GetMultiLineTextExtent(msg);
307 page_size = wxSize(std::min(msg_sz.GetX() + 2 * em, 68 * em),
308 std::min(msg_sz.GetY() + 2 * em, 68 * em));
309 }
310 html->SetMinSize(page_size);
311

315 if (monospaced_font)
316 // Code formatting will be preserved. This is useful for reporting errors from the placeholder parser.

◆ check_color_change()

bool Slic3r::GUI::check_color_change ( PrintObject *  object,
size_t  frst_layer_id,
size_t  layers_cnt,
bool  check_overhangs,
std::function< bool(Layer *)>  break_condition 
)
40{
41 double prev_area = area(object->get_layer(frst_layer_id)->lslices);
42
43 bool detected = false;
44 for (size_t i = frst_layer_id + 1; i < layers_cnt; i++) {
45 Layer *layer = object->get_layer(i);
46 double cur_area = area(layer->lslices);
47
48 // check for overhangs
49 if (check_overhangs && cur_area > prev_area && !equivalent_areas(prev_area, cur_area)) break;
50
51 // Check percent of the area decrease.
52 // This value have to be more than min_delta_area and more then 10%
53 if ((prev_area - cur_area > min_delta_area) && (cur_area / prev_area < 0.9)) {
54 detected = true;
55 if (break_condition(layer)) break;
56 }
57
58 prev_area = cur_area;
59 }
60 return detected;
61}

523 for (int i = 0; i <= resolution; ++i) {
524 const float angle = static_cast<float>(i) * step_angle;
525 append_vertex(entity, { inner_radius * ::sin(angle), inner_radius * ::cos(angle), -half_thickness }, -Vec3f::UnitZ());
526 }
527

531 }

535 append_indices(entity, 28 + 2 * resolution + i, 29 + 3 * resolution + i, 29 + 2 * resolution + i);
536 append_indices(entity, 29 + 2 * resolution + i, 29 + 3 * resolution + i, 30 + 3 * resolution + i);
537 }
538
539 // side faces vertices and triangles

543 const float s = ::sin(angle);
544 append_vertex(entity, { inner_radius * s, inner_radius * c, -half_thickness }, { -s, -c, 0.0f });
545 }
546

548 const float angle = static_cast<float>(i) * step_angle;

552 }
553
554 int first_id = 26 + 4 * (resolution + 1);

556 const int ii = first_id + i;
557 append_indices(entity, ii, ii + 1, ii + resolution + 2);
558 append_indices(entity, ii, ii + resolution + 2, ii + resolution + 1);
559 }
560
561 append_vertex(entity, { inner_radius, 0.0f, -half_thickness }, -Vec3f::UnitY());
562 append_vertex(entity, { outer_radius, 0.0f, -half_thickness }, -Vec3f::UnitY());
563 append_vertex(entity, { inner_radius, 0.0f, half_thickness }, -Vec3f::UnitY());
564 append_vertex(entity, { outer_radius, 0.0f, half_thickness }, -Vec3f::UnitY());
565

567 append_indices(entity, first_id, first_id + 1, first_id + 3);

569

571 const float angle = static_cast<float>(i) * step_angle;
572 const float c = ::cos(angle);

574 append_vertex(entity, { outer_radius * s, outer_radius * c, -half_thickness }, { s, c, 0.0f });
575 }
576

588 append_indices(entity, ii, ii + resolution + 2, ii + resolution + 1);

591 data.entities.emplace_back(entity);
592 return data;

41// Style_NoTrailingZeroes does not work on OSX. It also does not work correctly with some locales on Windows.
42// return wxNumberFormatter::ToString(value, max_precision, wxNumberFormatter::Style_NoTrailingZeroes);
43
44 wxString s = wxNumberFormatter::ToString(value, max_precision, wxNumberFormatter::Style_None);
45
46 // The following code comes from wxNumberFormatter::RemoveTrailingZeroes(wxString& s)
47 // with the exception that here one sets the decimal separator explicitely to dot.
48 // If number is in scientific format, trailing zeroes belong to the exponent and cannot be removed.
49 if (s.find_first_of("eE") == wxString::npos) {
50 char dec_sep = is_decimal_separator_point() ? '.' : ',';
51 const size_t posDecSep = s.find(dec_sep);
52 // No decimal point => removing trailing zeroes irrelevant for integer number.
53 if (posDecSep != wxString::npos) {
54 // Find the last character to keep.
55 size_t posLastNonZero = s.find_last_not_of("0");
56 // If it's the decimal separator itself, don't keep it either.
57 if (posLastNonZero == posDecSep)
58 -- posLastNonZero;
59 s.erase(posLastNonZero + 1);
60 // Remove sign from orphaned zero.
61 if (s.compare("-0") == 0)
62 s = "0";
63 }
64 }

497 std::vector<std::wstring> blacklisted_libraries;
498 BlacklistedLibraryCheck::get_instance().get_blacklisted(blacklisted_libraries);
499 for (const std::wstring& wstr : blacklisted_libraries) {
500 std::string utf8 = boost::nowide::narrow(wstr);
501 if (size_t last_bs_pos = utf8.find_last_of("\\"); last_bs_pos < utf8.size() - 1) {
502 // Remove anything before last backslash so we don't send the path to the DLL.
503 utf8.erase(0, last_bs_pos + 1);
504 }
505 pt::ptree node; // Create an unnamed node containing the value
506 node.put("", utf8);
507 blacklisted_node.push_back(std::make_pair("", node)); // Add this node to the list.
508 }
509 if (! blacklisted_libraries.empty())
510 data_node.add_child("Blacklisted libraries", blacklisted_node);

517 opengl_node.put("Vendor", OpenGLManager::get_gl_info().get_vendor());
518 opengl_node.put("Renderer", OpenGLManager::get_gl_info().get_renderer());
519 // Generate list of OpenGL extensions:
520 std::string extensions_str = gl_get_string_safe(GL_EXTENSIONS, "");
521 std::vector<std::string> extensions_list;
522 boost::split(extensions_list, extensions_str, boost::is_any_of(" "), boost::token_compress_off);
523 std::sort(extensions_list.begin(), extensions_list.end());
524 pt::ptree extensions_node;
525 for (const std::string& s : extensions_list) {
526 if (s.empty())
527 continue;
528 pt::ptree ext_node; // Create an unnamed node containing the value
529 ext_node.put("", s);
530 extensions_node.push_back(std::make_pair("", ext_node)); // Add this node to the list.
531 }
532 opengl_node.add_child("Extensions", extensions_node);
533 data_node.add_child("OpenGL", opengl_node);
534
535 pt::ptree root;
536 root.add_child("data", data_node);
537
538 // Now go through all the values and trim leading/trailing whitespace.
539 // Some CPU names etc apparently have trailing spaces...
540 std::function<void(pt::ptree&)> remove_whitespace;
541 remove_whitespace = [&remove_whitespace](pt::ptree& t) -> void
542 {
543 if (t.empty()) // Trim whitespace
544 boost::algorithm::trim(t.data());
545 else
546 for (auto it = t.begin(); it != t.end(); ++it)
547 remove_whitespace(it->second);
548 };
549 remove_whitespace(root);
550
551 // Serialize the tree into JSON and return it.
552 std::stringstream ss;
553 pt::write_json(ss, root);
554 return ss.str();
555}

static void Slic3r::GUI::generic_exception_handle ( )
static
921{
922 // Note: Some wxWidgets APIs use wxLogError() to report errors, eg. wxImage
923 // - see https://docs.wxwidgets.org/3.1/classwx_image.html#aa249e657259fe6518d68a5208b9043d0
924 //
925 // wxLogError typically goes around exception handling and display an error dialog some time
926 // after an error is logged even if exception handling and OnExceptionInMainLoop() take place.
927 // This is why we use wxLogError() here as well instead of a custom dialog, because it accumulates
928 // errors if multiple have been collected and displays just one error message for all of them.
929 // Otherwise we would get multiple error messages for one missing png, for example.
930 //
931 // If a custom error message window (or some other solution) were to be used, it would be necessary
932 // to turn off wxLogError() usage in wx APIs, most notably in wxImage
933 // - see https://docs.wxwidgets.org/trunk/classwx_image.html#aa32e5d3507cc0f8c3330135bc0befc6a
934/*#ifdef WIN32
935 //LPEXCEPTION_POINTERS exception_pointers = nullptr;
936 __try {
937 throw;
938 }
939 __except (CBaseException::UnhandledExceptionFilter2(GetExceptionInformation()), EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
940 //__except (exception_pointers = GetExceptionInformation(), EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
941 // if (exception_pointers) {
942 // CBaseException::UnhandledExceptionFilter(exception_pointers);
943 // }
944 // else
945 throw;
946 }
947#else*/
948 try {
949 throw;
950 } catch (const std::bad_alloc& ex) {
951 // bad_alloc in main thread is most likely fatal. Report immediately to the user (wxLogError would be delayed)
952 // and terminate the app so it is at least certain to happen now.
953 BOOST_LOG_TRIVIAL(error) << boost::format("std::bad_alloc exception: %1%") % ex.what();
954 flush_logs();
955 wxString errmsg = wxString::Format(_L("OrcaSlicer will terminate because of running out of memory."
956 "It may be a bug. It will be appreciated if you report the issue to our team."));
957 wxMessageBox(errmsg + "\n\n" + wxString(ex.what()), _L("Fatal error"), wxOK | wxICON_ERROR);
958
959 std::terminate();
960 //throw;
961 } catch (const boost::io::bad_format_string& ex) {
962 BOOST_LOG_TRIVIAL(error) << boost::format("Uncaught exception: %1%") % ex.what();
963 flush_logs();
964 wxString errmsg = _L("OrcaSlicer will terminate because of a localization error. "
965 "It will be appreciated if you report the specific scenario this issue happened.");
966 wxMessageBox(errmsg + "\n\n" + wxString(ex.what()), _L("Critical error"), wxOK | wxICON_ERROR);
967 std::terminate();
968 //throw;
969 } catch (const std::exception& ex) {
970 wxLogError(format_wxstr(_L("OrcaSlicer got an unhandled exception: %1%"), ex.what()));
971 BOOST_LOG_TRIVIAL(error) << boost::format("Uncaught exception: %1%") % ex.what();
972 flush_logs();
973 throw;
974 }
975//#endif
976}

bool Slic3r::GUI::get_data_from_svg ( const std::string &  filename,
unsigned int  max_size_px,
ThumbnailData &  thumbnail_data 
)
152{
153 bool compression_enabled = false;
154
155 NSVGimage *image = nsvgParseFromFile(filename.c_str(), "px", 96.0f);
156 if (image == nullptr) { return false; }
157
158 float scale = (float) max_size_px / std::max(image->width, image->height);
159
160 thumbnail_data.width = (int) (scale * image->width);
161 thumbnail_data.height = (int) (scale * image->height);
162
163 int n_pixels = thumbnail_data.width * thumbnail_data.height;
164
165 if (n_pixels <= 0) {
166 nsvgDelete(image);
167 return false;
168 }
169
170 NSVGrasterizer *rast = nsvgCreateRasterizer();
171 if (rast == nullptr) {
172 nsvgDelete(image);
173 return false;
174 }
175
176 // creates the temporary buffer only once, with max size, and reuse it for all the levels, if generating mipmaps
177 std::vector<unsigned char> data(n_pixels * 4, 0);
178 thumbnail_data.pixels = data;
179 nsvgRasterize(rast, image, 0, 0, scale, thumbnail_data.pixels.data(), thumbnail_data.width, thumbnail_data.height, thumbnail_data.width * 4);
180
181 // we manually generate mipmaps because glGenerateMipmap() function is not reliable on all graphics cards
182 int lod_w = thumbnail_data.width;
183 int lod_h = thumbnail_data.height;
184 GLint level = 0;
185 while (lod_w > 1 || lod_h > 1) {
186 ++level;
187
188 lod_w = std::max(lod_w / 2, 1);
189 lod_h = std::max(lod_h / 2, 1);

171 MDT_RAW_DPI_ = 2,
172 MDT_DEFAULT_ = MDT_EFFECTIVE_DPI_,
173 };

175 // Need strong types for winapi_get_function() to work
176 struct GetDpiForWindow_t { typedef HRESULT (WINAPI *FN)(HWND hwnd); };
177 struct GetDpiForMonitor_t { typedef HRESULT (WINAPI *FN)(HMONITOR hmonitor, MONITOR_DPI_TYPE_ dpiType, UINT *dpiX, UINT *dpiY); };

181
182 // Desktop Window is the window of the primary monitor.
183 const HWND hwnd = (window == nullptr) ? ::GetDesktopWindow() : window->GetHandle();
184
185 if (GetDpiForWindow_fn != nullptr) {
186 // We're on Windows 10, we have per-screen DPI settings
187 return GetDpiForWindow_fn(hwnd);
188 } else if (GetDpiForMonitor_fn != nullptr) {
189 // We're on Windows 8.1, we have per-system DPI
190 // Note: MonitorFromWindow() is available on all Windows.
191

193 UINT dpiX;
194 UINT dpiY;

196 } else {
197 // We're on Windows earlier than 8.1, use DC
198
199 const HDC hdc = GetDC(hwnd);
200 if (hdc == NULL) { return DPI_DEFAULT; }
201 return GetDeviceCaps(hdc, LOGPIXELSX);
202 }
203#elif defined __linux__
204 // TODO
205 return DPI_DEFAULT;
206#elif defined __APPLE__
207 // TODO
208 return DPI_DEFAULT;
209#else // freebsd and others
210 // TODO
211 return DPI_DEFAULT;
212#endif

◆ get_utf8_seq_length() [1/2]

static int Slic3r::GUI::get_utf8_seq_length ( const char *  seq,
size_t  size 
)
static
594{
595 int length = 0;
596 unsigned char c = seq[0];
597 if (c < 0x80) { // 0x00-0x7F
598 // is ASCII letter
599 length++;
600 }
601 // Bytes 0x80 to 0xBD are trailer bytes in a multibyte sequence.
602 // pos is in the middle of a utf-8 sequence. Add the utf-8 trailer bytes.
603 else if (c < 0xC0) { // 0x80-0xBF
604 length++;
605 while (length < size) {
606 c = seq[length];
607 if (c < 0x80 || c >= 0xC0) {
608 break; // prevent overrun
609 }
610 length++; // add a utf-8 trailer byte
611 }
612 }
613 // Bytes 0xC0 to 0xFD are header bytes in a multibyte sequence.
614 // The number of one bits above the topmost zero bit indicates the number of bytes (including this one) in the whole sequence.
615 else if (c < 0xE0) { // 0xC0-0xDF
616 // add a utf-8 sequence (2 bytes)
617 if (2 > size) {
618 return size; // prevent overrun
619 }
620 length += 2;
621 }
622 else if (c < 0xF0) { // 0xE0-0xEF
623 // add a utf-8 sequence (3 bytes)
624 if (3 > size) {
625 return size; // prevent overrun
626 }
627 length += 3;
628 }
629 else if (c < 0xF8) { // 0xF0-0xF7
630 // add a utf-8 sequence (4 bytes)
631 if (4 > size) {
632 return size; // prevent overrun
633 }
634 length += 4;
635 }
636 else if (c < 0xFC) { // 0xF8-0xFB
637 // add a utf-8 sequence (5 bytes)
638 if (5 > size) {
639 return size; // prevent overrun
640 }
641 length += 5;
642 }
643 else if (c < 0xFE) { // 0xFC-0xFD
644 // add a utf-8 sequence (6 bytes)
645 if (6 > size) {
646 return size; // prevent overrun
647 }
648 length += 6;
649 }
650 else { // 0xFE-0xFF
651 // not a utf-8 sequence
652 length++;
653 }
654 return length;
655}

27{
28#if __APPLE__
29 // On OSX, we use boost::process::spawn() to launch new instances of PrusaSlicer from another PrusaSlicer.
30 // boost::process::spawn() sets SIGCHLD to SIGIGN for the child process, thus if a child PrusaSlicer spawns another
31 // subprocess and the subrocess dies, the child PrusaSlicer will not receive information on end of subprocess
32 // (posix waitpid() call will always fail).
33 // https://jmmv.dev/2008/10/boostprocess-and-sigchld.html
34 // The child instance of PrusaSlicer has to reset SIGCHLD to its default, so that posix waitpid() and similar continue to work.
35 // See GH issue #5507

37#endif // __APPLE__

◆ picking_checksum_alpha_channel()

unsigned char Slic3r::GUI::picking_checksum_alpha_channel ( unsigned char  red,
unsigned char  green,
unsigned char  blue 
)
362{
363 // 8 bit hash for the color
364 unsigned char b = ((((37 * red) + green) & 0x0ff) * 37 + blue) & 0x0ff;
365 // Increase enthropy by a bit reversal
366 b = (b & 0xF0) >> 4 | (b & 0x0F) << 4;
367 b = (b & 0xCC) >> 2 | (b & 0x33) << 2;
368 b = (b & 0xAA) >> 1 | (b & 0x55) << 1;
369 // Flip every second bit to increase the enthropy even more.
370 b ^= 0x55;
371 return b;
372}

◆ short_and_splitted_time()

static std::string Slic3r::GUI::short_and_splitted_time ( const std::string &  time)
static
86{
87 // Parse the dhms time format.
88 int days = 0;
89 int hours = 0;
90 int minutes = 0;
91 int seconds = 0;
92 if (time.find('d') != std::string::npos)
93 ::sscanf(time.c_str(), "%dd %dh %dm %ds", &days, &hours, &minutes, &seconds);
94 else if (time.find('h') != std::string::npos)
95 ::sscanf(time.c_str(), "%dh %dm %ds", &hours, &minutes, &seconds);
96 else if (time.find('m') != std::string::npos)
97 ::sscanf(time.c_str(), "%dm %ds", &minutes, &seconds);
98 else if (time.find('s') != std::string::npos)
99 ::sscanf(time.c_str(), "%ds", &seconds);
100
101 // Format the dhm time.
102 char buffer[64];
103 if (days > 0)
104 ::sprintf(buffer, "%dd%dh\n%dm", days, hours, minutes);
105 else if (hours > 0) {
106 if (hours < 10 && minutes < 10 && seconds < 10)
107 ::sprintf(buffer, "%dh%dm%ds", hours, minutes, seconds);
108 else if (hours > 10 && minutes > 10 && seconds > 10)
109 ::sprintf(buffer, "%dh\n%dm\n%ds", hours, minutes, seconds);
110 else if ((minutes < 10 && seconds > 10) || (minutes > 10 && seconds < 10))
111 ::sprintf(buffer, "%dh\n%dm%ds", hours, minutes, seconds);
112 else
113 ::sprintf(buffer, "%dh%dm\n%ds", hours, minutes, seconds);
114 } else if (minutes > 0) {
115 if (minutes > 10 && seconds > 10)
116 ::sprintf(buffer, "%dm\n%ds", minutes, seconds);
117 else
118 ::sprintf(buffer, "%dm%ds", minutes, seconds);
119 } else
120 ::sprintf(buffer, "%ds", seconds);
121 return std::string(buffer);
122}

◆ slider_behavior()

bool Slic3r::GUI::slider_behavior ( ImGuiID  id,
const ImRect &  region,
const ImS32  v_min,
const ImS32  v_max,
ImS32 *  out_value,
ImRect *  out_handle,
ImGuiSliderFlags  flags,
const int  fixed_value,
const ImVec4 &  fixed_rect 
)
205{
206 ImGuiContext& context = *GImGui;
207 ImGuiIO& io = ImGui::GetIO();
208
209 const ImGuiAxis axis = (flags & ImGuiSliderFlags_Vertical) ? ImGuiAxis_Y : ImGuiAxis_X;
210
211 const ImVec2 handle_sz = out_handle->GetSize();
212 ImS32 v_range = (v_min < v_max ? v_max - v_min : v_min - v_max);
213 const float region_usable_sz = (region.Max[axis] - region.Min[axis]);
214 const float region_usable_pos_min = region.Min[axis];
215 const float region_usable_pos_max = region.Max[axis];
216
217 // Process interacting with the slider
218 ImS32 v_new = *out_value;
219 bool value_changed = false;
220
221 // drag behavior
222 if (context.ActiveId == id)
223 {
224 float mouse_pos_ratio = 0.0f;
225 if (context.ActiveIdSource == ImGuiInputSource_Mouse)
226 {
227 if (context.IO.MouseReleased[0])
228 {
229 ImGui::ClearActiveID();
230 }
231 if (context.IO.MouseDown[0])
232 {
233 const float mouse_abs_pos = context.IO.MousePos[axis];
234 mouse_pos_ratio = (region_usable_sz > 0.0f) ? ImClamp((mouse_abs_pos - region_usable_pos_min) / region_usable_sz, 0.0f, 1.0f) : 0.0f;
235 if (axis == ImGuiAxis_Y)
236 mouse_pos_ratio = 1.0f - mouse_pos_ratio;
237 v_new = v_min + (ImS32)(v_range * mouse_pos_ratio + 0.5f);
238 }
239 }
240 }
241 // click in fixed_rect behavior
242 if (ImGui::ItemHoverable(fixed_rect, id) && context.IO.MouseReleased[0])
243 {
244 v_new = fixed_value;
245 }
246
247 // apply result, output value
248 if (*out_value != v_new)
249 {
250 *out_value = v_new;
251 value_changed = true;
252 }
253
254 // Output handle position so it can be displayed by the caller
255 const ImS32 v_clamped = (v_min < v_max) ? ImClamp(*out_value, v_min, v_max) : ImClamp(*out_value, v_max, v_min);
256 float handle_pos_ratio = v_range != 0 ? ((float)(v_clamped - v_min) / (float)v_range) : 0.0f;
257 handle_pos_ratio = axis == ImGuiAxis_Y ? 1.0f - handle_pos_ratio : handle_pos_ratio;
258 const float handle_pos = region_usable_pos_min + (region_usable_pos_max - region_usable_pos_min) * handle_pos_ratio;
259
260 ImVec2 new_handle_center = axis == ImGuiAxis_Y ? ImVec2(out_handle->GetCenter().x, handle_pos) : ImVec2(handle_pos, out_handle->GetCenter().y);
261 *out_handle = ImRect(new_handle_center - handle_sz * 0.5f, new_handle_center + handle_sz * 0.5f);
262
263 return value_changed;
264}

44 args.reserve(4);
45 args.emplace_back(path.wc_str());

55 // just hang in the background.

78 args.emplace_back("--single-instance");

80 }
81 catch (const std::exception& ex) {

83 }

85#else // Linux or Unix

88 args.reserve(3);
89#ifdef __linux__

93 // see https://docs.appimage.org/packaging-guide/environment-variables.html#id2

101#endif // __linux__

105 my_path = (bin_path.parent_path() / ((instance_type == NewSlicerInstanceType::Slicer) ? "orca-slicer" : "bambu-gcodeviewer")).string();

)
static
116{
117 if (version == "N/A")
118 return false;
119
120 std::vector<std::string> tokens;
121 boost::split(tokens, version, boost::is_any_of(" "), boost::token_compress_on);
122
123 if (tokens.empty())
124 return false;
125

128

130 unsigned int gl_minor = 0;
131
132 if (numbers.size() > 0)
133 gl_major = ::atoi(numbers[0].c_str());
134
135 if (numbers.size() > 1)
136 gl_minor = ::atoi(numbers[1].c_str());
137
138 if (gl_major < major)
139 return false;
140 else if (gl_major > major)
141 return true;
142 else
143 return gl_minor >= minor;
144}

◆ wxImage_to_wxBitmap_with_alpha()

static wxBitmap Slic3r::GUI::wxImage_to_wxBitmap_with_alpha ( wxImage &&  image,
float  scale = 1.0f 
)
static
42{
43#ifdef __WXGTK2__
44 // Broken alpha workaround
45 wxMemoryOutputStream stream;
46 image.SaveFile(stream, wxBITMAP_TYPE_PNG);
47 wxStreamBuffer *buf = stream.GetOutputStreamBuffer();
48 return wxBitmap::NewFromPNGData(buf->GetBufferStart(), buf->GetBufferSize());
49#else
50#ifdef __APPLE__
51 // This is a c-tor native to Mac OS. We need to let the Mac OS wxBitmap implementation
52 // know that the image may already be scaled appropriately for Retina,
53 // and thereby that it's not supposed to upscale it.
54 // Contrary to intuition, the `scale` argument isn't "please scale this to such and such"
55 // but rather "the wxImage is sized for backing scale such and such".
56 return wxBitmap(std::move(image), -1, scale);
57#else
58 return wxBitmap(std::move(image));
59#endif
60#endif
61}
